<div class="wonderwrap">


<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Setup</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>7 coins</li>
                <li><u>Pantheon:</u> 3 Grand temples instead of 3 Guilds</li>
                <li><u>Agora:</u>
                    <ul>
                        <li>12 cubes each</li>
                        <li>add 5/5/3 Senator cards <i>after</i> discarding to box</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Turn Order</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Trigger <i>one</i> Conspiracy (optional, if available)</li>
                <li>Activate a Pantheon card OR play a card from structure to
                    <ul>
                        <li>Construct a building / Recruit a Senator</li>
                        <li>Discard for coins</li>
                        <li>Construct a Wonder</li>
                        <li>Prepare a Conspiracy (no cost)</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>



<h3>Reminders</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Discarding: $2, plus $1 per yellow card</li>
    <li>Buying resources: $2, plus $1 per brown/gray that opponent has (ignore yellow and Wonder production)</li>
    <li>Min $1 to buy a resource</li>
    <li>7 Wonders max, return 8th Wonder to box immediately after 7th construction</li>
    <li>Weaker military decides who starts each age; tie: player who took most recent turn decides</li>
    <li><u>Pantheon</u> Take a Token (Mythology or Offering) when you must flip the card it is on</li>
    <li><u>Agora</u> Some decrees start face-up, others face-down</li>
    <li><u>Agora</u> Recruiting a Senator costs $1 for each Senator you already have (0, 1, 2, ...)</li>
    <li>Tie: player with more points from blue buildings</li>
</ul>


<h3>Clarifications</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Cannot retrieve cards discarded during setup (Mausoleum, Hades)</li>
    <li>Military tokens: no further penalty for insufficient funds - lose all money</li>
    <li>Shipowners Guilds (brown/gray): pick 1 city for both cards, cannot count city A for brown and city B for gray</li>
    <li>For "destroy a card" attacks, the attacker chooses</li>
    <li><u>Pantheon</u> Mythology Tokens are <u>not</u> discarded when used to purchase grand temples</li>
    <li><u>Pantheon</u> Double or half prices <i>before</i> applying discounts</li>
    <li><u>Agora</u> Leave triggered conspiracies face-up with the Age card underneath it</li>
</ul>


