<h3>FAQ</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Shields are <u>not</u> considered instant effects, and losing a Wonder with shields also takes away the shields</li>
    <li>Symbols on Grand Temples are considered to be chains for purposes of Decrees and Progress tokens</li>
    <li>Placing/moving cubes is never mandatory</li>
    <li>Curia Julia Wonder allows a second conspiracy trigger on the turn it is built</li>
    <li>Upper left ability of a Wonder is ignored when Wonders are stolen</li>
    <li>Neptune: Apply the effect of token 2 against opponent, regardless of where it came from</li>
    <li>Coercion
        <ul>
            <li>both players get symbol pair: active player chooses token first</li>
            <li>both players get 6 science symbols: game ends immediately in a tie</li>
            <li>break a symbol pair: no progress discard</li>
            <li>opponent has no cards of color you want: may play it just to place a cube</li>
            <li>take card with Nisaba snake: snake token is discarded for no effect</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Treason: only the chosen card is revealed</li>
    <li>Espionage: only the chosen token is revealed</li>
    <li>Obscurantism: when choosing a token from the box, you need not reveal to opponent</li>
    <li>Sabotage: 8th Wonder stays in the box, if it had been placed there</li>
    <li>Turn of Events: may gain tokens from multiple cards on the same turn</li>
    <li>Extortion: Wonder is stolen but not constructed</li>
</ul>



